Discover 5 AI-enabled security solutions

In this activity, I explored several security solutions that use artificial intelligence to improve protection and detection of threats. These systems use AI to analyse patterns and identify unusual behaviour.

1. AI-based CCTV systems  
I explored how modern CCTV systems use AI to detect suspicious behaviour, such as unusual movement or loitering. Some systems can also recognise faces or track individuals, which helps improve monitoring and response.

2. Email spam and phishing filters  
I explored how email services like Gmail use AI to detect spam and phishing emails. These systems analyse patterns in emails and automatically filter suspicious messages into the spam folder, helping protect users from scams.

3. Fraud detection in banking  
I explored how banks use AI to detect unusual transactions. For example, if a transaction is very different from normal spending behaviour, the system may flag it or block it. This helps prevent fraud.

4. AI-based malware detection  
I explored how modern antivirus software uses AI to detect new types of malware. Instead of only relying on known signatures, AI can analyse behaviour and identify suspicious programs.

5. Deepfake detection tools  
I explored tools that use AI to detect deepfake images, videos, or audio. These systems analyse inconsistencies in media to determine whether the content is real or generated, which helps prevent misinformation and scams.

Overall, these examples show that AI is increasingly used in cybersecurity to detect threats more efficiently and respond to attacks in real time.
